28/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The founding assembly of the New Social Democracy of Serbia (NSS) party was held on Saturday (March 26th) in Belgrade. Its leader, Dusan Janjic, presented the party's platform, describing the NSS as a modern left-wing political organisation whose aim is to draft a strategic plan for Serbia's development and present a better vision for its future. (Beta, RTS, Radio Free Europe - 26/03/11)
